Your Honor,

I stand before you today to offer my sincere plea of guilty for the charge of being drunk and disorderly. I take full responsibility for my actions and acknowledge the impact they may have had on others present during that unfortunate incident.

On the day in question, I found myself in need of a day of relaxation and respite from the pressures of life. Regrettably, I turned to alcohol to find solace, which led to a lack of control and disruptive behavior. I deeply regret my actions and feel a profound sense of shame for my conduct.

I am aware that my age, being 54 years old, deviates from the usual age range associated with such behavior. Additionally, I have one previous conviction of careless driving from 10 years ago, which stands as a reminder of the consequences of my past actions. However, it is my earnest intention to learn from my mistakes and demonstrate personal growth.

Regarding rectifying the harm caused, I understand the significance of making amends. While I am not inclined to pursue counseling as a means of addressing my behavior, I am open to alternative suggestions that the court deems appropriate.

It is crucial for me to emphasize that I fully understand the gravity of my actions and the possible distress they may have caused to others. I genuinely feel remorseful for any distress I may have caused and pledge to make every effort to contribute positively to society moving forward.

In conclusion, Your Honor, I acknowledge and plead guilty to the charge, and I seek your guidance and leniency as we move forward in this legal process. I am committed to learning from this experience and becoming a better individual. I humbly request the court's consideration of these mitigating factors.

Thank you for your attention, Your Honor.

